This paper discusses the efficient implementation of groundness analysis in Prolog, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the design of an abstract domain and its impact on algorithmic complexity, which is related to logic in computer science (cs.LO). The use of Boolean functions and constraint logic programming also suggests a connection to software engineering (cs.SE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the iteration strategy and optimization techniques, which are related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
